column6: The process of extracting protein-rich fractions from crop products through dry milling and air-classification. The protein concentrates produced typically contain between 40-65% protein.

column6: The process of extracting protein-rich fractions from crop products through milling, alkaline extraction, precipitation, and drying. The protein isolates produced have a high purity (>90% protein) and low concentration of anti-nutritional factors. Unlike dry fractionation, this method necessitates the use of various chemicals and water.
column24: agri-food processor
